   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "283b439e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are missing values in `total_bill`, `tip`, `day`, and `size`. Since these are a small fraction of the ~250 rows:\n",
    "- For **numeric** columns (`total_bill`, `tip`), I fill missing values with the **median**, since a few extreme bills/tips could skew the mean.\n",
    "- For **`size`** (party size), I fill with the **mode** (most common party size), since it's a small whole number and the mode is a sensible default.\n",
    "- For **`day`** (categorical, no obvious default), I **drop** the rows, since there's no reliable way to infer which day a visit happened on."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "c9dda185",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-07-13T21:56:26.714396Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-07-13T21:56:26.714248Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-07-13T21:56:26.724310Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-07-13T21:56:26.723167Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "total_bill    0\n",
       "tip           0\n",
       "sex           0\n",
       "smoker        0\n",
       "day           0\n",
       "time          0\n",
       "size          0\n",
       "dtype: int64"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df = df.dropna(subset=['day']).copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "df['total_bill'] = df['total_bill'].fillna(df['total_bill'].median())\n",
    "df['tip'] = df['tip'].fillna(df['tip'].median())\n",
    "\n",
    "df.isnull().sum()"
   ]
